# Chapter 7: Strategy Implementation

## Annual Objectives (FY 2026 – FY 2028)
To operationalize the long-term goals and QSPM priorities (Product Development and Market Penetration), Cosco establishes strict annual targets:
* **FY 2026 (Stabilization & Inventory Liquidation):** Achieve sales P33.0 million; reduce cost of sales to 86%; convert P5.0 million of idle raw material inventory into institutional deliveries; cut net operating loss to P1.0 million.
* **FY 2027 (Turnaround & Automation Integration):** Achieve sales P39.0 million; reduce cost of sales to 80% via CNC machinery deployment; generate positive Net Income of P3.0 million; pay down trade payables by P8.0 million.
* **FY 2028 (Sustainable Growth & Expansion):** Achieve sales P45.0 million; maintain cost of sales below 75%; achieve Net Income of P6.0 million; eliminate reliance on stockholder working capital advances.

## Operational & Functional Policies
* **Inventory & Procurement Policy:** Implement a mandatory Just-In-Time (JIT) material staging protocol. Raw material procurement exceeding P500,000 requires direct sign-off from the COO to prevent inventory bottlenecks.
* **Bidding Compliance Policy:** Standardize public procurement proposals to mandate a minimum projected gross margin of 25% on institutional contracts (such as SSS bids) prior to submission.
* **Green Manufacturing Policy:** Mandate that at least 35% of all new product lines utilize reclaimed wood, bamboo, or recycled metal finishes by late 2027.

## Resource Allocation & Capital Budgeting
Reallocating stockholder advances (P15.4M) and internal operational cash flow toward high-return capital investments:
* **Production Automation Allocation (P6.5 Million):** Upgrade the Bacoor facility with automated CNC cutting tools and robotic assembly units over 24 months to address labor inefficiencies.
* **Digital MIS & ERP Allocation (P1.8 Million):** Deploy an enterprise SAP/cloud inventory management system to integrate sales forecasts with factory procurement.
* **R&D Innovation Allocation (P2.5 Million):** Fund prototyping for built-in smart office electronics and biophilic workspace installations.

## Matching Structure to Strategy
To execute a focused differentiation strategy, Cosco must shift from an informal family-led hierarchy to a **Strategic Business Unit (SBU) Matrix Structure**:
* **Manufacturing SBU (Bespoke & Wellness):** Dedicated entirely to custom institutional projects and product innovation.
* **Commercial Trading SBU:** Dedicated to standardized wholesale/retail catalog distribution and digital platforms.
* **Centralized Corporate Services:** Executive oversight under COO Linda V. Dela Cruz retaining consolidated control over Finance, HRAD, and Regulatory Compliance.

## Performance & Pay to Strategy
* **Executive & Sales Incentives:** Tie sales commission structures directly to *realized gross profit margins* rather than raw top-line sales volume to stop margin dilution.
* **Production Productivity Bonuses:** Implement factory-floor reward systems tied to material scrap reduction and on-time order fulfillment.

## Conflict Management & Organizational Change
* **Addressing Resistance to Automation:** Deploy transparent cross-training programs for the 26 registered employees, upskilling manual craftsmen into automated CNC equipment technicians.
* **Inter-Departmental Alignment:** Establish weekly operational reviews connecting sales bidding teams with factory production heads to ensure order timelines match raw material readiness.
